  <div class="site-main" id="top">
    <section class="hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="section-kicker">Practical AI systems for messy business workflows</p>
        <h2>Bring one slow process. Leave with a pilot plan.</h2>
        <p>
          Conneen AI builds custom assistants, automations, dashboards, and software tools that reduce repetitive work, improve throughput, and keep expert judgment in the loop.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <button class="site-button primary return-chat-trigger" type="button">Run workflow diagnostic</button>
          <a class="site-button" href="#pilots">See example pilots</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="consulting-panel" aria-label="AI pilot diagnostic preview">
        <div class="panel-top">
          <p class="panel-label">Diagnostic output</p>
          <p class="panel-title">From bottleneck to first useful pilot.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="signal-list">
          <div class="signal-item">
            <span class="signal-num">01</span>
            <span>
              <strong>Workflow described</strong>
              Emails, calls, PDFs, spreadsheets, reports, quotes, schedules, or intake tasks.
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-item">
            <span class="signal-num">02</span>
            <span>
              <strong>Automation opportunity</strong>
              Classify the workflow, identify tools/data, and find the highest-leverage intervention.
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="signal-item">
            <span class="signal-num">03</span>
            <span>
              <strong>Pilot recommendation</strong>
              A narrow first build with human review, clear inputs, and measurable operational value.
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="problems">
      <p class="section-kicker">Where AI can actually help</p>
      <h3>Start with the work your team repeats every week.</h3>
      <p>
        The best first AI project is usually not a giant transformation. It is one annoying, recurring workflow where information moves slowly, gets copied by hand, or depends on scattered knowledge.
      </p>

      <div class="cards problem-cards">
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-num">01</span>
          <strong>Manual data entry</strong>
          <p>Turn emails, forms, PDFs, notes, and spreadsheets into structured records your team can review.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-num">02</span>
          <strong>Slow quoting or estimating</strong>
          <p>Draft quotes, collect missing details, check rules, and keep a person in control of final approval.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-num">03</span>
          <strong>Scattered company knowledge</strong>
          <p>Create internal assistants that answer from SOPs, documents, spreadsheets, policies, and business rules.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-num">04</span>
          <strong>Reporting bottlenecks</strong>
          <p>Automate recurring reports, dashboards, exception lists, and weekly operational summaries.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-num">05</span>
          <strong>Document-heavy review</strong>
          <p>Classify, compare, summarize, and route technical documents while preserving expert review.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <span class="card-num">06</span>
          <strong>Scheduling and coordination</strong>
          <p>Help teams triage requests, recommend next actions, and reduce manual follow-up loops.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section diagnostic-section" id="diagnostic">
      <div>
        <p class="section-kicker">AI pilot finder</p>
        <h3>The chatbot is the front door to scoping the work.</h3>
        <p>
          Describe one repetitive process. The diagnostic should classify the workflow, ask what tools and data are involved, suggest a narrow first pilot, and produce a summary that can become a lead or consultation brief.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="diagnostic-card">
        <span class="console-line">&gt; analyze workflow bottleneck</span>
        <span class="console-line muted">workflow type: document / email / spreadsheet / scheduling / reporting</span>
        <span class="console-line muted">pilot shape: extract → structure → draft → human review → output</span>
        <button class="site-button primary return-chat-trigger" type="button">Open diagnostic</button>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="pilots">
      <p class="section-kicker">Example pilots</p>
      <h3>From messy workflow to working system.</h3>
      <p>
        These are the kinds of narrow, practical pilots that help prove value before a larger build.
      </p>

      <div class="pilot-grid">
        <article class="pilot-card">
          <p class="pilot-label">Email intake</p>
          <h4>Inbox chaos → structured task queue</h4>
          <p><strong>Before:</strong> Requests arrive by email and get copied into a spreadsheet.</p>
          <p><strong>After:</strong> The system extracts request type, urgency, customer, location, and suggested next action for review.</p>
          <p><strong>First pilot:</strong> Email parser + review dashboard + notification flow.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="pilot-card">
          <p class="pilot-label">Document review</p>
          <h4>Large files → summarized action list</h4>
          <p><strong>Before:</strong> Staff manually read technical documents to find changes, issues, or requirements.</p>
          <p><strong>After:</strong> AI classifies, summarizes, compares, and flags items for expert review.</p>
          <p><strong>First pilot:</strong> Document classifier + extraction rules + approval queue.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="pilot-card">
          <p class="pilot-label">Reporting</p>
          <h4>Recurring reports → automated operational signal</h4>
          <p><strong>Before:</strong> Someone gathers spreadsheets, cleans data, and sends the same report every week.</p>
          <p><strong>After:</strong> Data is validated, exceptions are highlighted, and the report is drafted automatically.</p>
          <p><strong>First pilot:</strong> Spreadsheet ingestion + exception report + dashboard.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="pilot-card">
          <p class="pilot-label">Internal knowledge</p>
          <h4>Scattered answers → company assistant</h4>
          <p><strong>Before:</strong> Employees ask around or dig through files to find the right rule, process, or precedent.</p>
          <p><strong>After:</strong> A private assistant answers from approved company knowledge and cites source materials.</p>
          <p><strong>First pilot:</strong> Knowledge base ingestion + internal Q&amp;A assistant.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="industries">
      <p class="section-kicker">Strong-fit teams</p>
      <h3>Built for operationally complex businesses.</h3>
      <div class="cards compact-cards">
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Contractors & field service</strong>
          <p>Estimates, work orders, inspections, dispatch, customer follow-up, and recurring admin.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Property operations</strong>
          <p>Maintenance requests, lease data, vendor coordination, tenant communication, and reporting.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Technical documentation</strong>
          <p>Document comparison, classification, technical-data workflows, and review support.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Government-adjacent teams</strong>
          <p>Careful, auditable, human-reviewed tools for document-heavy operational processes.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Fisheries, wildlife, energy & geospatial</strong>
          <p>Field data, maps, reporting, forecasting, and operational decision support.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Small business operations</strong>
          <p>Replace fragile spreadsheet and inbox processes with lightweight internal tools.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section process-section" id="process">
      <p class="section-kicker">Pilot process</p>
      <h3>Start small. Prove value. Expand only when it works.</h3>
      <div class="timeline">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <strong>Process map</strong>
          <p>Identify the repetitive workflow, decision points, inputs, outputs, and failure points.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <strong>Pilot scope</strong>
          <p>Choose one narrow automation target with clear success criteria and review rules.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <strong>Prototype</strong>
          <p>Build a working version using real or representative data from your process.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>04</span>
          <strong>Human review</strong>
          <p>Keep your team in control of approvals, edits, exceptions, and high-impact decisions.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>05</span>
          <strong>Measure impact</strong>
          <p>Compare time saved, throughput, reliability, accuracy, and bottleneck reduction.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section trust-section" id="trust">
      <p class="section-kicker">Trust</p>
      <h3>AI that supports your team instead of bypassing it.</h3>
      <p>
        Conneen AI does not build black-box systems that blindly replace expert judgment. The goal is to draft, organize, check, recommend, and accelerate work while preserving human control where it matters.
      </p>
      <div class="trust-list">
        <span>Human review by default for high-impact workflows</span>
        <span>Practical pilots instead of massive transformation promises</span>
        <span>Tools designed around your current process and constraints</span>
        <span>Privacy and data handling discussed before implementation</span>
      </div>
    </section>

